    <note>Chen(1) Yi [55] Jiansu's [7102] (qv.) son. Chen(1) Yanmo [7132] is listed, in one source, as the father-in-law of Wu(3) Shunzhi [4024], the great grandsons of Wu(3) Fang [4012], who was the brother of Wu(3) Chong [1960] and Wu(3) Yu [8165], and Chen(1) Yi [55] is listed as his grandfather-in-law in another source. Hong(1) [53] is listed as Yanmo's [7132] father in yet another source. The sons of both Hong [53] and Yi [55] are Yan x and grandsons are Jing-x. Yi and Hong are either brothers or cousins. Yi was Xie(1) Tao's [7105] grandson-in-law, Xie(1) Lun's [7034] son-in-law, Yao(1) Fu's [7100] father-in-law, Rao(1) Meng's [7112] grandfather-in-law. He recommended Ren(1) Zhongzheng [875] as his own replacement (zidai) when he was transferred from Hebei yunshi to Shanxi yunshi. XCB, 211.2b, 219.2b; Su Song, WJ, 60.1a-7b. CBD, 3, 2527.</note>
